@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

Um. It's an mp3 decoder. 

As fast or faster than amp, but with much better compatiblity for
different mp3 streams, as well as layer I and II support.

This is another in a long line of Cstarware (see the faq on Darxide).

@ENDNODE


@NODE "History" "History"

24th march 1997
    - First release to aminet
    - -l and -r options are buggy and enforcer hit like hell.
	Options have been hidden from user.
    - FPU versions only until I sort my gcc problems.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

    - an amiga
    - ixemul.library v45.1+
    - an FPU

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "Usage"

2 versions supplied. Compiled with different gcc options. Rename to suit
your needs.

    maplay.020881 - 020+ with FPU (-m68020 -m68881)
    maplay.040881 - 040 with FPU


Usage:
    maplay -s spot1.mp3 > spot1.pcm

Or just:
    maplay
	to get a list of options.


Warning! Mpeg audio files are often compressed at ratios greater than 10:1,
so you better make sure you have lots of HD space to decode them.

If you output as PCM you will need to specify the type of file when
playing back with play16. eg

    play16 freq=44100 tracks=2 bits=16 spot1.pcm

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Playback" "Playback"

At the moment there are no amiga audio routines in the code.
To play the sound you must first decode to disk and then play with play16.
I tried fiddling with pipes and play16, but play16 won't play sound from a
pipe.  There may be other sound players out there you could try this with,
but i'm not certain.

When AHI V3 arrives I'm told we will have an AUDIO: device similar to AUD:
(audio-handler on aminet) but with support for 14bit 44khz playback.  Have
to wait and see.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Speed" "Speed"

The file spot1.mp3 has been used for timing tests. It is a 10.9 second
stereo 44.1khz 16bit sample.

25Mhz030/881 decodes it in 6minutes 14seconds.

[not super accurate timing]
[No other timings are available]

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Source" "Source"

The source code to maplay was written by @{" lots of people " link "Acknowledgements"}

The original source is available from http://www.abts.net/~heffe/mp3/

My changes to this source are in the src directory of this archive. Just
copy my files over the ones in the distribution.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Problems" "Problems"

	
    - Immediate guru when run
	Make sure you have the latest ixemul.library from aminet.
	(version 45.1 is the latest)

    - EMT trap
	This will happen when you run a version of maplay requiring an FPU
	but don't actually have an FPU on your machine.  

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Feedback" "Feedback"

Feedback if you want to give it:

    - Do you care whether it requires ixemul.library or not?
    - Do you have any experience in putting ASM code into gcc code?
    - Any general suggestions?
    - How long does it take your computer to decode 'spot1.mp3'? File
	available from http://www.netforward.com/cryogen/?mikecheng
    - Which processor do you have and which one of the exe's do you use?

Contact @{"me" link "Author"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Future" "Future"

    - compile for specific processors. (namely 060)
	Unfortunately gcc doesn't yet have an 060 optimization option.
	SAS/C does though, so someone may want to send me an 060 binary
	to include, or release it to aminet.

    - Fix single channel decode options to not cause enforcer hits.
	At the moment the -l and -r options of the original source have
	been 'hidden'. This is because they cause enforcer hits really
	bad.

    - Figure out my gcc/FPU problems.
	Everything I compile with gcc seems to want an FPU, regardless
	of whether I actually have the -m68881 switch.

@ENDNODE


